  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Three-wheelers to register with police for fuel; 49CC Bikes to register with DMT for Fuel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); All Three-Wheeler drivers have been requested to register their Three-Wheelers at their respective area Police Stations & nominate One Fuel Station before the 31st July.",
        "Minister of Power and Energy Kanchana Wijesekera tweeted that from the 1st of August Three-Wheeler will only be allowed to obtain fuel from the their registered Fuel Station.",
        "He also requested all users of Garden Equipment, Generators & other equipment requiring fuel to register their requirements in their respective Divisional secretariats with their weekly fuel requirements & to nominate One Fuel station to obtain the requirement.",
        "\u201cVehicle users that cannot register with the chassis number will be able to register with the revenue license from Friday,\u201d he added.",
        "The Minister also said that users of 49CC bikes have to register with the Department of Motor Traffic to obtain their licenses & register with National Fuel Pass",
        "Three-wheelers to register with police for fuel; 49CC Bikes to register with DMT for Fuel"
      ],
